  "url": "https://www.ada.lk/breaking_news/\u0db6\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd4-\u0db4\u0dde\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba-\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8-\u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0da7-\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca-\u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dda/11-396787",
  "time_ut": 1661947407,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db6\u0dd0\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dd4 \u0db4\u0dde\u0daf\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dab\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8 \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0db3\u0dd4\u0db8\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db1\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Bank privatization is not a solution to the crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "43 Division Leader, Member of Parliament Patali Champika Ranawaka says that privatizing banks without applying the law to the people who destroyed the banks is not a solution to the crisis.",
        "He also points out that privatization of public institutions will not solve everything.",
        "Regarding the management of public expenditure, Mr. Ranawaka further emphasized that all public institutions should be subjected to a management audit during the budget debate in Parliament today (31) regarding the budget speech delivered by the President as Finance Minister. He also explained the importance of working under the policy of 'one institution for one job', pointing out that it can reduce the number of government institutions in the country to about 2/3.",
        "In addition, Mr. Ranawaka pointed out the possibility of improving the efficiency of the public service by creating a process of evaluation of institutions, starting with department heads and conducting a 'work audit', giving practical examples of his work as a minister. Mr. Ranawaka also presented his suggestions regarding increasing the technical efficiency of government institutions and identifying new sources of income.",
        "\"According to the budget statement presented by the President, all receipts in the year 2022 are 2384 billion rupees. All expenses, including loans, are 6222 billion rupees. That means there is an expenditure of two rupees and sixty cents for one rupee of income in his budget.",
        "Last April 12, the government suspended the payment of foreign loans and made a statement that they will not repay the loans of the main financial institutions, that is, the World Bank, the Asian Development Bank, and the Asian Infrastructure Bank.",
        "I don't know whether the suspended loan is included in this cost or not. That amount of suspended loans is a whopping $4 billion this year. Therefore, I think the Minister of Finance and the Honorable President will announce whether the presented budget includes it or not.\""
      ],
